erfaces and event type constants:\n- `OrderEvent`, `OrderCreatedEvent`, `OrderCancelledEvent`, `OrderRefundedEvent`, `PaymentChargedEvent`, `StockReservedEvent`\n- `ORDER_EVENTS` object with event name constants\n\n#### /workspace/src/events/bus.ts\nEventBus class that implements pub/sub pattern:\n- Uses module-level `globalHandlers` Map to store handlers\n- Methods: `on()`, `off()`, `emit()`, `clear()`\n- **BUG FOUND:** Uses `globalHandlers` Map instead of instance-level storage, causing state to persist across EventBus instances\n\n#### /workspace/src/orders/repository.ts\nOrderRepository for CRUD operations on orders:\n- Stores orders in a Map\n- Methods: `create()`, `findById()`, `update()`, `findByCustomer()`, `findByStatus()`, `clear()`\n- **BUG FOUND:** The `update()` method doesn't preserve existing fields - it creates a new object with only the `id` and `updatedAt` from the updates\n\n#### /workspace/src/orders/service.ts\nOrderService for order lifecycle management:\n- Constructor takes: OrderRepository, EventBus, BillingService\n- Methods: `createOrder()`, `cancelOrder()`, `refundOrder()`, `getOrder()`, `getOrdersByCustomer()`\n- REFUND_WINDOW_DAYS = 30\n- Emits events: ORDER_EVENTS.CREATED, ORDER_EVENTS.CONFIRMED, ORDER_EVENTS.CANCELLED, ORDER_EVENTS.REFUNDED\n- **BUG FOUND:** `cancelOrder()` expects `order.items` to exist but it may be undefined\n\n#### /workspace/src/inventory/repository.ts\nInventoryRepository for stock management:\n- Stores stock records in a Map\n- Methods: `setStock()`, `getStock()`, `reserve()`, `release()`, `clear()`\n- Tracks available and reserved quantities\n\n#### /workspace/src/inventory/service.ts\nInventoryService for event-driven inventory:\n- Registers handlers for ORDER_EVENTS.CREATED and ORDER_EVENTS.CANCELLED\n- Handles stock reservation and rollback on failure\n- **BUG FOUND:** `handleOrderCancelled()` checks for `eventWithItems.status !== 'cancelled'` and returns early if true, but the status is being set AFTER the event is emitted\n\n#### /workspace/src/billing/service.ts\nBillingService for payment processing:\n- Stores payment records in a Map\n- Constructor takes: EventBus, NotificationService\n- Methods: `registerHandlers()`, `chargePayment()`, `issueRefund()`, `getPayment()`, `clear()`\n- **BUG FOUND:** `handleRefund()` is a private method without `this` binding context, causing `this.payments` to be undefined when called as an event handler\n\n#### /workspace/src/billing/calculator.ts\nCalculates order totals with discount and tax:\n- Function: `calculateOrderTotal(items, discountPercent, taxRate)`\n- Returns: `PriceBreakdown` with subtotal, discountAmount, taxAmount, total\n- Includes rounding logic\n- **BUG FOUND:** Rounding calculation for multiple item orders is incorrect - results in 130.87 instead of 130.86\n\n#### /workspace/src/notifications/service.ts\nNotificationService for sending notifications:\n- Maintains notification templates and sent history\n- Methods: `sendConfirmation()`, `sendCancellation()`, `sendRefundNotice()`, `getSentNotifications()`, `clear()`\n\n### 5. ALL TEST FILES (COMPLETE CONTENT)\n\n#### /workspace/tests/events.test.ts\n5 tests for EventBus:\n- Emits events to registered handlers\n- Supports multiple handlers for same event\n- Doesn't fire handlers for different events\n- Removes handlers with off()\n- Clears all handlers\n**Status:** All 5 PASSING\n\n#### /workspace/tests/notifications.test.ts\n4 tests for NotificationService:\n- Sends order confirmation\n- Sends cancellation notice\n- Sends refund notice\n- Tracks all sent notifications\n**Status:** All 4 PASSING\n\n#### /workspace/tests/inventory.test.ts\n5 tests for InventoryService:\n- Reserves stock on order.created\n- Throws when stock is insufficient\n- Rolls back partial reservations on failure\n- Releases stock on order.cancelled (FAILING)\n- Reserves stock for concurrent orders independently (FAILING)\n**Status:** 3 passing, 2 failing\n\n#### /workspace/tests/billing.test.ts